Generate exactly one Java rule method body for a CalcStage.POST ModuleAlgBase rule method.
Requirements:
- Return only Java statements for the method body.
- Do not include package, imports, class declarations, annotations, method declarations,
  markdown, or explanations.
- @CodeRuleAnno(calcStage = CalcStage.POST), method name, method header, and rule identifier
  are generated by RuleTrans templates.
- Use only POST instance-view APIs such as currentInst(), parameter(code), part(code),
  partCategory(code), partCategorySum(code), value(), setValue(...), dynAttr(...),
  setDynAttr(...), sumQuantity(), and sumDynAttr4Int(...).
- For numeric writeback to parameters, wrap numeric values with String.valueOf(...).
- For category-scoped parameter writeback, use partCategory("categoryCode").parameter("paraCode").setValue(...).
- For category-scoped part writeback, use partCategory("categoryCode").part("partCode").setQuantity(...)
  or partCategory("categoryCode").part("partCode").setDynAttr(...).
- Use partCategory("categoryCode").sumQuantity() for category quantity totals.
- Use partCategorySum("categoryCode") only for dynamic-attribute aggregation such as
  sumDynAttr4Int("attrCode"), dynAttr("attrCode"), or dynAttrs("attrCode").
  Do not call partCategorySum("categoryCode").sumQuantity() or .quantity().
- Do not use constraint-model APIs such as model(), para(...), partVar(...),
  partCategoryVar(...), onlyEnforceIf(...), addLessOrEqual(...), inCompatible(...),
  or updatePriorityObjectFuntion(...).

Valid example:
int sum = partCategorySum("drive").sumDynAttr4Int("Capacity");
parameter("pDriveSumCapacity").setValue(String.valueOf(sum));
int qty = partCategory("drive").sumQuantity();
parameter("pDriveQuantity").setValue(String.valueOf(qty));
